Use the standard library
This is how to f of n:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Remember that fact is 1
   Do this n times:
      Increase i
      Remember that fact is product of fact and i
      When i is 5, then:
         Add result to 15
      But, if not:
         When i is 7, then:
            Add result to 28
         But, if not:
            Add result to fact
         End when
      End when
   End do
   The answer is result
